<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:lang="en" xml:id="fplot2d">
  <info>
    <pubdate>$LastChangedDate$</pubdate>
  </info>
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>fplot2d</refname>
    <refpurpose>2D plot of a curve defined by a
  function</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>
    <synopsis>fplot2d(xr,f,[style,strf,leg,rect,nax])
fplot2d(xr,f,&lt;opt_args&gt;)</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Arguments</title>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>xr</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>vector.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>f</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>external of type <literal>y=f(x)</literal> i.e. a scilab function or
          a dynamically linked routine referred to as a string.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>style,strf,leg,rect,nax</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>see <literal>plot2d</literal></para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>&lt;opt_args&gt;</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>see <literal>plot2d</literal></para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para><literal>fplot2d</literal> plots a curve defined by the external function
    <literal>f</literal>. The curve is approximated by a piecewise linear
    interpolation using the points <literal>(xr(i),f(xr(i))</literal>. The values of
    f(x) are obtained by <literal>feval(xr,f)</literal>.</para>
    <para>Enter the command <literal>fplot2d()</literal> to see a demo.</para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Examples</title>
    <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[ 
deff("[y]=f(x)","y=sin(x)+cos(x)")
x=[0:0.1:10]*%pi/10;
fplot2d(x,f)
clf();
fplot2d(1:10,'parab')
 ]]></programlisting>
  </refsection>
